And this message that I'm about to preach is part one of two and part two is tonight at five.

00:59.919 --> 01:06.125
So we're gonna look today in this morning's service at verses 12, 13 and 14 and tonight at verses 15 and 16.

01:06.565 --> 01:11.449
And we'll share much of the working vision of the church tonight in the evening service.

01:11.469 --> 01:14.652
We're gonna share about 40 or 50 major goals of the church.

01:14.952 --> 01:17.735
We're gonna talk about some of our strategic plan.

01:18.155 --> 01:19.837
We're gonna share our core values.

01:19.877 --> 01:23.620
We have a great service plan tonight and a lot of things to put into your hands.

01:23.600 --> 01:25.502
lot of devotional materials as well.

01:25.963 --> 01:31.408
On your way out of this service you're going to receive a copy of the church calendar and don't forget to pick that up.

01:31.629 --> 01:33.911
A lot of times we'll have a meeting like coming up in October.

01:33.931 --> 01:47.526
We'll have maybe a missions conference and someone will say I didn't know about that and I'll say I gave you the calendar date 225 days ago and so be sure to get the calendar kind of work your schedule around it and put the Lord right in the middle of all the things we do in the new year.

01:47.946 --> 01:52.811
Well let's read together if you would follow with me Philippians 3 verse number 12.

01:53.192 --> 01:53.572
This is the

01:53.552 --> 02:08.548
Apostle Paul writing to the church at Philippi, not as though I had already attained either were already perfect, but I follow after if that I may apprehend that for which also I am apprehended of Christ Jesus.

02:09.349 --> 02:21.842
Brethren, I count not my life myself to have apprehended, but this one thing I do, forgetting those things which are behind and reaching forth under those things which are before

02:22.306 --> 02:30.723
I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.

02:31.164 --> 02:42.546
I want to draw your attention to the phrase in verse 13 that says, reaching forth unto those things which are before, and I'd like to speak to you this morning on that subject.

02:42.690 --> 02:43.692
reaching forth.

02:43.812 --> 02:44.594
Let's pray together.

02:45.035 --> 02:49.283
Father, we thank You this morning for the infallible Word of God that we hold in our hands.

02:49.744 --> 02:52.870
We are blessed to have Your Word, Your message, Your guide for us.

02:53.471 --> 03:00.705
Help us to hear it gladly today and help us to reach forth this morning with faith that You will work in 2020.

03:01.106 --> 03:04.132
And I pray and ask this in Jesus' name, amen.

03:04.152 --> 03:05.074
You may be seated.

03:06.274 --> 03:17.930
Well, the Apostle Paul often used athletic metaphors to describe the spiritual journey that he was enjoying and to challenge others on their spiritual journey as well.

03:18.470 --> 03:20.793
He had seen many of the sites of the ancient games.

03:20.833 --> 03:30.226
He had seen the Colosseums at Athens and he had seen no doubt the Colosseum at Rome and other places such a Corinth.

03:30.274 --> 03:48.493
And he understood, as the Holy Spirit gave him these words, how to apply an athletic metaphor such as reaching forth, someone that's moving into a race and challenging them to approach the Christian life, not with a lackadaisical attitude, but with a spirit of faith in God.

03:49.033 --> 03:57.522
And all of us, as we gather here this morning, early on in 2020, we're standing at the beginning point at the starting line for a brand new year.

03:57.826 --> 04:07.809
And I do believe it's important that we have not just a powerful positive mindset, but a biblical mindset as we enter into this new season of life.

04:07.929 --> 04:08.751
I don't know about you.

04:08.791 --> 04:11.217
I'm still having trouble writing 2020, right?

04:11.277 --> 04:16.850
Just trying to get accustomed to the fact that here we are at 2020 at the beginning of this time.

04:17.378 --> 04:25.665
And I think many of you perhaps have had a few days as I have these last few weeks to just ponder what are some of the goals for the new year.

04:25.765 --> 04:36.875
Some of those goals that you might think about may have to do with family time or maybe with your health or maybe with your finances and just exactly what do we need to accomplish in 2020.

04:36.935 --> 04:39.097
Terry and I were talking the other day.

04:39.137 --> 04:43.260
We thought we talked about maybe joining Weight Watchers this year.

04:43.300 --> 04:47.364
And I said, yeah, I could bring the donuts to the first meeting and kind of welcome everybody

04:47.344 --> 04:50.069
and she said that would not be a good idea.

04:50.150 --> 04:53.937
And some people think about the physical things like that.

04:54.117 --> 04:59.308
One man was asked what his New Year's resolutions were, and he replied, I really don't know.

04:59.348 --> 05:00.570
My wife hasn't told me yet.

05:00.610 --> 05:02.294
And some of you understand that as well.

05:02.334 --> 05:08.466
So all of us putting these lists together, thinking about where are we heading in 2020?

05:08.834 --> 05:18.384
But this morning we see a very poignant passage of scripture that can give direction to all of us with respect to reaching forth into 2020.

05:18.625 --> 05:29.597
This particular passage was written by the Apostle Paul to a group of believers in northern Macedonia, northern Greece, a place that was very impoverished.

05:30.057 --> 05:38.066
It was a place that was suffering under Roman rule, a city about nine miles from the agency northwest of the island of Theos,

05:38.370 --> 05:44.277
And this particular region always amazes me, especially the first century history of it, because they were impoverished.

05:44.297 --> 05:46.300
They were going through difficult times.

05:46.480 --> 05:55.651
And yet, from this place of Philippi, there was a Christian church established that raised up and became a powerful lighthouse for the gospel.

05:56.071 --> 05:58.494
They were difference makers in their society.

05:58.795 --> 06:04.542
Although poverty abounded, they were one of the most generous churches ever to be written about in the Bible.

06:04.782 --> 06:08.146
They met needs every time they possibly could.

06:08.450 --> 06:10.536
And so the Apostle Paul came to the city.

06:11.077 --> 06:18.418
Now here's how it was to go into a city and go to the Jewish synagogue and begin reasoning and debating about Jesus Christ as the Messiah.

06:18.754 --> 06:21.617
This particular city, however, did not have a synagogue.

06:22.037 --> 06:25.601
Many historians believe they were perhaps anti-Semitic.

06:25.641 --> 06:31.046
Whatever the reason it may have been, Paul went into the city realizing there was no synagogue.

06:31.066 --> 06:39.013
He goes to the riverside, another gathering place, and he begins preaching the gospel, the death, burial, and resurrection of Jesus Christ.

06:39.033 --> 06:48.082
And I like sometimes to get the background of a book of the Bible and to know a little bit about what the context is, and it's interesting to see how churches get started.

06:48.258 --> 06:59.186
And so when we study the context of the church at Philippi, the first one we read about, going back to the book of Acts, chapter number 16 and verse 14, we read about the first convert at Philippi.

06:59.234 --> 07:01.636
And it was a lady, and her name was Lydia.

07:01.696 --> 07:02.877
She was a business woman.

07:03.257 --> 07:05.660
The Bible describes her as a seller of purple.

07:06.160 --> 07:11.385
And she would go down near the seashore, and she would find these particular shells that were there.

07:11.485 --> 07:18.010
And these particular shells had some chemical extract that she would create purple garments with.

07:18.331 --> 07:20.552
And so she became a seller of purple.

07:20.953 --> 07:29.220
And as she was there near the river, and where the ocean would come in, collecting the shells, she no doubt heard Paul preaching the death zone resurrection and the Bible

07:29.200 --> 07:33.049
says that she believed on the Lord Jesus Christ with all of her heart.

07:33.671 --> 07:40.487
Well, if you read more in Acts 16, you read the next person that came into the church of all people was a demon possessed girl.

07:41.108 --> 07:43.474
She was the subject of human trafficking.

07:43.714 --> 07:49.842
The men that were her owners were using her in a work of divination to try to foretell the future.

07:49.922 --> 07:52.345
And they were using her, taking advantage of her.

07:52.425 --> 07:54.668
And the Apostle Paul saw what was happening.

07:55.009 --> 07:58.253
And in the name of Jesus Christ, she was loose from the demonic powers.

07:58.613 --> 08:00.536
She received Christ as her savior.

08:00.776 --> 08:04.000
And as I said a moment ago, greater is he that is in you than he that is in the world.

08:04.281 --> 08:08.306
My friend, when Jesus comes into your life, no demon can ever take your life again.

08:08.482 --> 08:12.274
And her life was radically changed by the gospel of Jesus Christ.

08:12.635 --> 08:18.354
So now we have a business woman and a struggling young woman who's coming out of a terrible life of her past.

08:18.466 --> 08:25.052
And then we read a little further and we meet the third member of the church at Philippi and he was the Philippian jailer.

08:25.492 --> 08:32.378
And remember Paul and Silas the song said a moment ago, they were in jail because people didn't like them preaching the gospel.

08:32.638 --> 08:37.182
So they were in jail and while they were there the Bible says at midnight they were singing praise to God.

08:37.422 --> 08:48.452
They were blessing his name and suddenly an earthquake comes and Paul and Silas are walking out and the jailer was fearful for his life because jailers could lose their life if the prisoners escaped.

08:48.432 --> 08:50.936
came to the Apostle Paul with that famous question.

08:50.956 --> 08:53.039
He said, sirs, say it with me.

08:53.420 --> 08:56.825
What must I do to be saved?

08:58.147 --> 08:59.569
That's the greatest question of life.

09:01.172 --> 09:03.816
And so many churches have so many answers to that question.

09:05.118 --> 09:11.528
And Paul said to him, very simply, believe on the Lord Jesus Christ and now shall be saved in all that house.

09:12.570 --> 09:15.474
And that jailer believed on the Lord Jesus Christ

09:15.618 --> 09:38.758
He was saved gloriously, and there you have the beginning of the church, a businesswoman, a demon possessed, formerly demon possessed girl, and a jailer, and they got together and impacted a region of the world for Jesus Christ, and I love that because folks, when we really get right down to it, in this auditorium this morning, we're just common folks, we're just sinners who've been saved by the grace of God.

09:38.778 --> 09:45.604
There's jailkeepers in here, and there's business women in here, and there's people with a lot of past in here, and been through lots of problems,

09:45.584 --> 09:47.510
and difficulties in their life.

09:47.530 --> 09:48.794
What do we have in common?

09:48.814 --> 09:54.974
We have Jesus in common, and with Jesus in common, we can see great things done for the glory of God.

09:55.897 --> 09:57.522
And that's what we learn at Philippi.

09:57.666 --> 10:02.230
we learn about the power of the gospel of Jesus Christ.

10:02.290 --> 10:14.781
And so Paul is writing to them and he's challenging these new believers that they would reach forth in their quest for Jesus, in their quest for knowing Jesus, in their quest for serving the Lord Jesus Christ.

10:14.861 --> 10:20.125
And in his challenge, he gives them three simple principles that I wanna give you this morning.

10:20.446 --> 10:24.269
Because I wanna see Lancaster Baptist reach our area for Christ.

10:24.409 --> 10:27.652
I wanna see our church make a great difference for the glory

10:27.632 --> 10:36.964
God so that no honest history is written of the city of Lancaster without mentioning the work of this single church that we would reach our potential for the glory of God.

10:37.165 --> 10:38.687
How can that be accomplished?

10:39.127 --> 10:42.232
Well three things Paul shares and I give them to you this morning first.

10:43.093 --> 10:48.260
We must enter this year with a spirit of humility.

10:49.621 --> 10:54.027
Now go ahead and write it down because it's a good word just to meditate on humility.

10:54.908 --> 10:56.050
You see a lot of the

10:56.194 --> 11:01.141
psychosibernetics of this world, the power of positive thinking, they kind of approach it the other way.

11:01.422 --> 11:06.910
They tell us that we should look ourselves in the mirror and pump ourselves up saying, we're great, we can handle it, we can get it done.

11:07.190 --> 11:09.293
But the Bible seems to go the opposite way.

11:09.534 --> 11:18.267
And the Bible says, no, if we're gonna get anything done spiritually, then we need to start with humility, which is to simply say, without God, I can't get anything done.

11:19.388 --> 11:20.730
Now, why do we say humility?

11:20.770 --> 11:21.992
Well, let's take a look at verse 12.

11:22.032 --> 11:23.154
What does Paul say?

11:23.330 --> 11:26.738
not as though I had already attained."

11:27.439 --> 11:33.673
Look at verse 13, brethren, I count not myself to have apprehended.

11:33.693 --> 11:36.299
Now what a humble admission.

11:37.161 --> 11:42.994
We won't take all the time, but if you studied Paul's life, he was school in the school of Gamaliel, a tremendous education.

11:43.234 --> 11:46.018
As a Pharisee, he was touching the law.

11:46.118 --> 11:47.040
He was righteous.

11:47.080 --> 11:49.384
He had memorized whole books of the Bible.

11:49.444 --> 11:51.327
He was an amazing leader.

11:51.407 --> 11:53.270
He was an amazing soldier.

11:53.871 --> 11:58.398
And yet he sets all of that aside and he says, but I have not arrived.

11:58.578 --> 12:01.422
And if any of us are going to grow this year, we've got to come to that place.

12:01.482 --> 12:02.925
We can't say, I've done this.

12:03.105 --> 12:03.746
I've been there.

12:03.866 --> 12:04.928
I have this education.

12:05.168 --> 12:09.315
What we need to say this morning is I'm a student sitting at the feet of Jesus Christ.

12:10.476 --> 12:11.538
I have not arrived.

12:12.322 --> 12:13.877
I don't have all the answers.

12:14.706 --> 12:16.786
I haven't been through every season of life.

12:16.898 --> 12:18.840
I haven't been to every planet to know.

12:18.860 --> 12:20.622
I haven't attained every degree.

12:21.102 --> 12:22.864
I have much to learn.

12:22.924 --> 12:24.726
Paul says, I have not attained.

12:24.806 --> 12:26.748
I have not yet apprehended.

12:26.828 --> 12:31.613
And Peter said, for God resisted the proud, but He gives grace to the humble.

12:31.633 --> 12:33.135
And we need God's grace this year.

12:33.175 --> 12:38.520
And that's only going to come as we humble ourselves before the Lord and as we admit that we need His help.

12:38.941 --> 12:43.986
You know, lifeguards tell us that the hardest person to save is a person trying to save themselves.

12:45.218 --> 12:53.292
When a lifeguard swims out to that person that is struggling and perhaps about to drown, the first thing they say to that person is, hey, look, just relax.

12:54.013 --> 12:55.716
Just let me bring you in.

12:55.936 --> 12:57.579
Stop trying to save yourself.

12:57.599 --> 13:00.564
Can I tell you this morning, you cannot save your own soul.

13:00.624 --> 13:03.890
Only Jesus can pay the price for your sin.

13:04.674 --> 13:06.979
And you cannot solve all of your own problems.

13:06.999 --> 13:13.054
There comes a point in time when you say, I only have so many resources, but I have not apprehended God.

13:13.314 --> 13:14.096
I need your help.

13:14.136 --> 13:16.983
It was a humble admission that was made here.

13:17.264 --> 13:19.308
It was a very honest admission.

13:19.770 --> 13:21.754
He says, either we're already perfect.

13:21.774 --> 13:23.378
He said, I'm not perfect.

13:23.682 --> 13:27.788
In fact, he says in 1 Corinthians 15 and I am the least of the apostles.

13:27.848 --> 13:28.449
And I know how it is.

13:28.489 --> 13:30.351
Sometimes we come to church and we should.

13:30.411 --> 13:31.233
We try to look right.

13:31.273 --> 13:32.034
We try to act right.

13:32.054 --> 13:33.295
We try to hold our Bibles right.

13:33.315 --> 13:34.317
So all these different things.

13:34.517 --> 13:38.783
But let's just come to this place to say, it doesn't matter what you're looking like today.

13:38.803 --> 13:41.367
It doesn't matter where you went to school, how much money's in your bank.

13:41.387 --> 13:43.990
Look at all of us are at the same starting point today.

13:44.251 --> 13:46.233
We all need God's help this year.

13:47.635 --> 13:50.640
In fact, the Bible says without him, we can do nothing.

13:50.860 --> 13:52.402
So it's a very humble admission.

13:52.610 --> 13:56.194
for the Apostle Paul to say, I count not myself to have apprehended.

13:56.214 --> 14:03.603
And can I say that sometimes the hardest people to get to understand this are those of us who've been Christians a long time?

14:04.304 --> 14:06.126
Because we can get to thinking, well, I know that.

14:06.226 --> 14:06.887
I've learned that.

14:06.967 --> 14:08.029
I've got these standards.

14:08.109 --> 14:09.911
I'm more holy and righteous.

14:09.991 --> 14:13.615
And what we need to recognize is none of us have arrived.

14:13.936 --> 14:16.339
All of us need to learn in the new year.

14:16.659 --> 14:18.021
And so it was a humble admission.

14:18.061 --> 14:19.783
It was also an honest admission.

14:20.363 --> 14:22.546
He says, either we're already perfect

14:22.850 --> 14:27.538
You see, no one is ever going to be saved if they have never confessed the fact that they're a sinner.

14:27.998 --> 14:32.606
You see, the Bible says for all have sinned and comes short of the glory of God.

14:33.347 --> 14:43.204
Every single one of us, if we're saved, have had a point where we've said to the Lord, Lord, I confess to you that I am a sinner and I ask you to be my Savior because the church can't save us from our sin.

14:43.464 --> 14:45.988
The baptistry water can't save us from our sin.

14:46.329 --> 14:49.554
The fact is that only Jesus Christ can save us from our sin.

14:50.082 --> 14:54.690
The Bible says, for whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

14:54.730 --> 14:57.426
But we must humble ourselves before the Lord.

14:57.858 --> 14:59.299
You say, well, I have been saved.

14:59.339 --> 15:00.320
I've trusted Christ.

15:00.340 --> 15:09.088
Well, then may I say that if you're going to be able to lead in this new year, if you're going to be able to serve more effectively in this new year, that we also must say, I've got a lot to learn.

15:09.128 --> 15:10.469
I've got a lot of listening to do.

15:10.769 --> 15:15.934
Moses said to God, when God said, I want you to go into Pharaoh, Moses said, who am I that I should go to Pharaoh?

15:16.214 --> 15:18.876
And that I should bring forth the children of Israel out of Egypt.

15:19.297 --> 15:20.838
Moses said, I'm not qualified for this.

15:20.978 --> 15:21.619
I don't know what to do.

15:21.899 --> 15:24.781
God, if you don't go with me, I'm not going to go, he said.

15:25.082 --> 15:26.923
And that ought to be your prayer in mind this year.

15:27.304 --> 15:27.844
Lord, if you

15:27.824 --> 15:28.605
don't go with me.

15:28.945 --> 15:32.049
I'm not going to go because I cannot make it without you."

15:32.069 --> 15:35.313
It was an honest assessment that Paul the Apostle made.

15:35.753 --> 15:37.976
He was humble in his assessment.

15:37.996 --> 15:39.518
And may we have that spirit.

15:39.938 --> 15:45.305
But not only was it an honest assessment, I want you to notice there letter B, that Paul became easy to direct.

15:46.666 --> 15:47.848
He was easy to lead.

15:47.988 --> 15:53.234
Now notice in verse 12, it says, not as though I had already attained, either were already perfect,

15:53.890 --> 15:56.339
But I follow after.

15:56.440 --> 15:57.764
Would you say that phrase with me, please?

15:58.106 --> 16:05.714
But I follow after if that I may apprehend that for which also I am apprehended of Christ.

16:05.890 --> 16:07.592
He says, I follow after.

16:07.652 --> 16:11.857
Now what he's telling us here, he says, I haven't apprehended Christ yet.

16:12.178 --> 16:14.881
I'm not like him to the extent that I want to be.

16:15.181 --> 16:17.965
I don't know him to the extent that I need to know him.

16:18.285 --> 16:20.288
But he said, I'm following after him.

16:20.648 --> 16:21.710
I'm looking to him.

16:21.990 --> 16:23.271
He is my goal.

16:23.632 --> 16:25.674
I'm easily directed to him.

16:25.935 --> 16:27.837
He has my attention.

16:28.077 --> 16:30.280
One of my favorite verses in the Bible is Ephesians 5-1.

16:30.681 --> 16:35.026
It says, be, therefore, followers of God as dear children.

16:35.426 --> 16:38.350
In other words, follow God like a child would follow you.

16:38.931 --> 16:55.095
We had some wonderful time last week with our grandchildren and we went swimming and we played games and did some different things and at night I got to tell them some Bible stories and you know the great thing about being with children that are four or five and six and seven years old is that when you say, all right, it's time for a Bible story.

16:55.296 --> 16:56.818
They want to hear the Bible story.

16:57.026 --> 16:58.088
It's time for a walk.

16:58.148 --> 16:59.210
They want to go on the walk.

16:59.671 --> 17:00.673
All these different things.

17:00.813 --> 17:03.880
Children just seem to eat right out of your hand, don't they?

17:03.900 --> 17:05.863
They want to know what the Bible says.

17:05.904 --> 17:08.970
They want to know some stories and learn these truths.

17:08.990 --> 17:12.617
And God says to all of us, that's how I want you to be this year.

17:13.158 --> 17:15.282
I want you to be easy to direct.

17:15.490 --> 17:20.796
I want you to follow God like a child would follow, and to have a tenderness toward the things of God.

17:21.136 --> 17:36.353
And in this hard world, in this argumentative world, in this divided world, we need to have a heart that is not jaded, but a heart that is tender to God, and so we're to follow after Christ, easily following, and then apprehending God's purpose.

17:36.393 --> 17:40.558
He says that I may apprehend that for which also I am apprehended for Christ Jesus.

17:41.219 --> 17:44.242
In other words, the God who came to us through His Son,

17:44.642 --> 17:49.148
The God who apprehended us wants us to apprehend him.

17:49.869 --> 17:51.531
You see, the Bible says we love him.

17:51.591 --> 17:52.032
Why?

17:52.072 --> 17:54.615
Because he first loved us.

17:54.996 --> 17:55.877
He came to us.

17:56.598 --> 18:02.927
And Paul says, since God came to me, I want to keep running to him and running to him.

18:02.947 --> 18:06.451
I want to be easily directed to him.

18:06.952 --> 18:14.322
And so the first way that we start this new year, as we come to this starting line, we say, Lord, I've not yet arrived.

18:15.266 --> 18:16.688
I've got to have your help this year.

18:17.829 --> 18:20.093
Approach this year with humility.

18:20.633 --> 18:21.715
How many of you are with me so far?

18:22.596 --> 18:23.717
Approach it right there with humility.

18:23.778 --> 18:26.161
Secondly, what's the second bit of advice he gave to them?

18:26.882 --> 18:29.645
The second word I want you to write down is the word focus.

18:30.667 --> 18:31.588
The word focus.

18:32.369 --> 18:44.786
Now notice that in verse 13, brethren, I count not myself to have apprehended, there's humility, but this one thing I do, let's read that phrase together, ready to begin, but this

18:46.818 --> 18:47.599
There's the focus.

18:48.640 --> 18:53.286
He says, I haven't arrived, but there's this one thing I'm going to do.

18:54.287 --> 19:02.437
Now, may I submit to you this morning that often our trouble is a lack of focus, not a lack of time.

19:03.839 --> 19:11.509
Now, I've said this too and you have, boy, if I could just have another 24 hours in a day and most people, if they had it, would squander it like they did the other 24.

19:11.629 --> 19:15.794
Our need is not always more time,

19:16.322 --> 19:19.446
Our need is often more in the way of focus.

19:19.526 --> 19:22.590
Paul said, this one thing I'm going to do.

19:23.111 --> 19:28.779
There have been books written on this subject, management books on this subject of finding your one thing and doing it well.

19:29.540 --> 19:33.044
And I believe that's derived from this biblical principle, this one thing.

19:33.205 --> 19:37.330
And Paul's one thing was Christ and knowing Christ.

19:37.570 --> 19:43.498
I read an amazing book over the last few weeks entitled Digital Minimalism by Cal Newport.

19:43.978 --> 19:46.482
I'd recommend every parent of a teenager get the book, by the way.

19:46.542 --> 19:50.327
It's not a Christian book, secular book, digital minimalism.

19:51.268 --> 20:02.322
It challenges the reader to focus our online time to a smaller number of apps and activities that serve the greater purposes of our life.

20:03.202 --> 20:08.352
It challenges the reader to be more focused in the area of social media.

20:08.492 --> 20:19.574
It teaches how the creators of Facebook use psychological methods to give users a little dopamine hit whenever they get a like or give someone else a like.

20:20.215 --> 20:23.922
And it talks about a lot of the science and psychology that

20:23.970 --> 20:45.749
has been employed by the creators of the social media sites, this psychology of addiction that has created such a culture into which that the average American spends 57 minutes a day, not using Facebook wisely, but just spending time on Facebook to have that little hit back of some form of acceptance.

20:45.809 --> 20:53.956
And the author of the book challenges the reader to optimize their use and to live with more intentionality in their

20:53.936 --> 20:55.037
every day life.

20:55.577 --> 20:59.201
Well, this is the greater theme of what the Apostle Paul is saying here.

20:59.781 --> 21:03.144
He's saying, there is a great intention that I have in this life.

21:03.765 --> 21:16.315
There is an intentionality about me that there is one major focus and everything else must be subservient to this one major focus of my life and the major focus was knowing Christ.

21:16.335 --> 21:21.420
He said, forgetting those things which are behind me and reaching forth under those things which are before.

21:21.480 --> 21:23.922
He said, this is the one thing that I'm going to do.

21:24.322 --> 21:28.427
Now, if you've read the verse before, you know that his one thing has two parts, doesn't it?

21:28.447 --> 21:30.670
So let's look at that there in verse 13.

21:30.710 --> 21:37.118
He says, but this one thing I do, first of all, he says, forgetting those things which are behind, forgetting the past.

21:38.219 --> 21:46.589
Now, I don't know how last year went for you and really, I don't think it really matters in the sense of failures or even sometimes successes.

21:47.691 --> 21:53.778
You see, the fact is that every one of us at a new year have the opportunity to forget those past failures.

21:54.370 --> 21:58.716
and to come to a place where we put those things behind us.

21:58.776 --> 22:01.940
And there are many in this room that need to learn how to be good forgetters.

22:02.060 --> 22:04.384
We need to learn how to put some things behind us.

22:04.424 --> 22:08.369
And I've learned in counseling and different settings that it's actually amazing.

22:08.389 --> 22:18.022
Some people can bring what I call their gunnysack full of hurts and problems, and they can remember things from seven years ago and five years ago and six months ago, and he said, here it comes, boy, it's out on the table.

22:19.304 --> 22:23.890
And can I encourage you that if you've been hurt, that you might

22:24.226 --> 22:30.226
be challenged this morning not to ruin your future by living in your past.

22:30.246 --> 22:34.962
Now Paul could have lived in his past because before he was a Christian he was a persecutor of the church.

22:35.362 --> 22:42.552
When he became a Christian, he was on the road to Damascus as he was heading up the road to Damascus and the light of Christ shone upon him.

22:43.012 --> 22:44.795
He was involved in persecuting the church.

22:44.855 --> 22:46.257
He had brought much havoc to the church.

22:46.457 --> 22:47.538
He could have regretted that.

22:47.578 --> 22:48.840
He could have lived in that past.

22:49.080 --> 22:51.083
But he said, I'm going to forget the past.

22:51.123 --> 22:52.966
I'm going to forget the past hurts.

22:53.006 --> 22:55.689
I'm going to forget the past failures that I've had.

22:55.930 --> 22:59.154
And I want to encourage you to set those things aside as well.

22:59.810 --> 23:05.499
Michael Jordan, one of the greatest basketball players that ever played, he said, I've missed more than 9,000 shots in my career.

23:06.120 --> 23:07.622
I've lost almost 300 games.

23:07.682 --> 23:12.750
On 26 occasions, I was entrusted to take the game-winning shot and I missed.

23:13.691 --> 23:19.961
I have failed over and over and over again in my life, and that is precisely why I succeed.

23:20.381 --> 23:26.150
And I want to encourage you, friend, I thank the Lord for my fifth grade school teacher who taught me that little poem.

23:26.391 --> 23:28.594
If at first you don't succeed, what is it?

23:28.674 --> 23:30.577
Try, try again.

23:30.918 --> 23:32.100
Paul said, you know what?

23:32.120 --> 23:36.809
I'm going to put my failures behind me, forgetting those things which are behind me.

23:37.009 --> 23:38.331
Let me encourage a friend.

23:38.351 --> 23:41.337
You say, Pastor, I fell into some sin last year.

23:41.697 --> 23:46.366
And what a tragedy when Satan tempts us and when perhaps sin has come into our life.

23:46.546 --> 23:50.994
But let me tell you what, if you're saved today, your sin is under the blood of Jesus Christ.

23:51.618 --> 23:54.460
If you're saved today, you're not saved because you earned it.

23:54.781 --> 23:56.142
It was a gift given to you.

23:56.502 --> 24:00.025
In fact, the Bible says concerning sin Psalm 103 and verse 12.

24:00.406 --> 24:04.910
As far as the east is from the west, so far hath he removed our transgression for us.

24:05.130 --> 24:10.414
What I'm trying to tell you this morning is God's not thinking about your sin and you don't need to be thinking about it.

24:10.634 --> 24:12.696
You need to thank God for his forgiveness.

24:12.916 --> 24:18.882
If we confess our sin, he is faithful and just to forgive us of our sin and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

24:18.902 --> 24:21.604
What I'm saying this morning is don't ruin your future.

24:21.584 --> 24:23.727
by living in your past."

24:24.288 --> 24:26.030
Paul said, I've got to forget the past.

24:26.711 --> 24:33.220
Here we see a man that was forgetting the past and then he was noticed this, reaching to the future, verse 13 again.

24:33.540 --> 24:37.425
He says, I reach forth to those things which are before.

24:37.465 --> 24:42.672
Now friend this morning, you are either hanging on or you are reaching forth.

24:43.033 --> 24:45.096
And I meet people all the time that are just hanging on.

24:45.716 --> 24:46.758
Just waiting for retirement.

24:47.859 --> 24:49.842
Just waiting for the bailout.

24:50.370 --> 24:52.054
They're just kind of hanging on in life.

24:52.094 --> 24:55.722
And I want to challenge you, don't just hang on, reach forward.

24:55.742 --> 25:03.378
You are either living a life of passive consumption, or you are living a life of intentional pursuit for God.

25:03.938 --> 25:08.307
You're either biting your time or you're going forth on purpose for the Lord.

25:08.548 --> 25:13.999
And Paul said, I'm reaching forth with this purpose, like a runner crossing the finish line.

25:14.260 --> 25:15.523
I'm stretching for it.

25:15.743 --> 25:20.674
In fact, he was, I believe in his mind, thinking of that day when he would see Jesus Christ.

25:20.834 --> 25:24.562
And let me tell you something, friend, we're all gonna see the Lord Jesus someday.

25:25.538 --> 25:40.671
The Bible says in 2 Timothy 4 and verse 8, henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness which the Lord the righteous judge shall give me at that day and not to me only, but unto all of them also that love his appearing.

25:41.031 --> 25:44.194
You see Paul was pressing toward that mark.

25:44.214 --> 25:46.816
As he stood at the line, he stood there with humility.

25:46.937 --> 25:48.338
Lord, I need your help.

25:48.678 --> 25:51.801
I can't do this on my own, but he stood there with focus.

25:51.901 --> 25:55.524
Lord, this one thing I do, I'm pressing forward

25:55.504 --> 25:58.450
to know you more, to serve you more, to love you more.

25:58.631 --> 26:00.775
That's the one dominant thing in my life.

26:01.036 --> 26:02.920
Business is good, and sports are fun.

26:03.241 --> 26:11.378
All the other things are important, but there's one great, great thing in my life, and that is knowing the Lord, and I want to encourage you this year.

26:11.682 --> 26:28.058
while there may be many trivial pursuits and many needful pursuits in your life, that you would make the Lord the main pursuit of your life, knowing Him, knowing that you're saved, knowing more of His guidance through His Word, that you would reach forth in this way.

26:28.318 --> 26:36.265
We see a man challenging the church, but God challenging us to have humility as we begin, to have focus as we begin.

26:36.426 --> 26:37.887
And let me give you one more word and we'll be done.

26:37.967 --> 26:41.010
Thirdly, to have the right goals as we begin.

26:41.538 --> 26:42.559
to have the right goals.

26:42.579 --> 26:48.426
Now look at verse 14, he says, I press toward the mark.

26:48.446 --> 26:49.107
Notice that word.

26:49.828 --> 26:53.453
I press toward the mark that speaks of the goal of his life.

26:53.593 --> 26:59.780
I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.

27:00.701 --> 27:03.265
Now again, I hope you've had some time to write out some goals.

27:04.126 --> 27:07.730
I've written goals out for my personal life, my family life,

27:07.842 --> 27:08.683
for the church.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.306
I've written out goals for the college.

27:10.627 --> 27:11.428
They're in writing.

27:11.548 --> 27:14.353
I've put action items behind each of those goals.

27:14.453 --> 27:15.936
And I think it's important.

27:15.976 --> 27:18.400
Someone once said, life is like a muddy jar.

27:18.500 --> 27:21.385
Sometimes you only see clearly when you sit still.

27:22.066 --> 27:29.298
And I hope you've had some time to sit still and let some things settle and really plan some goals.

27:29.378 --> 27:33.585
I'm sure some of those goals, as I said earlier, might be around some physical things.

27:33.605 --> 27:35.508
I heard of one woman this week.

27:35.568 --> 27:38.432
She said, my favorite thing to do at the gym is to leave.

27:40.416 --> 27:42.459
That's probably a reflection on her goals.

27:43.160 --> 27:45.524
One fella said, I'm on a strict running program.

27:45.584 --> 27:47.887
I started yesterday and I've only missed one day so far.

27:48.649 --> 27:50.532
And so that's kind of how goals go.

27:51.253 --> 27:54.638
If you don't put some action items behind them, maybe have some accountability.

27:55.760 --> 27:57.042
And goals are necessary.

27:57.282 --> 28:04.174
But when it comes to this overreaching goal, concerning Christ, I want to challenge you in two ways as we close.

28:04.274 --> 28:07.820
First, set eternal goals.

28:10.345 --> 28:14.552
Press toward the mark speaks of the mark of seeing Christ.

28:15.353 --> 28:22.706
Colossians 3-1, if you then be risen with Christ, seek those things which are above where Christ siteth on the right hand of God.

28:23.202 --> 28:30.249
As your goal must be supported by actions, if you want to know the Lord in the new year, then settle this matter of your salvation.

28:30.689 --> 28:34.213
Has there been a day in your life when you were born into the family of God?

28:34.773 --> 28:36.175
And if not, why not now?

28:36.895 --> 28:40.659
When by faith, you would say, I'm going to accept Christ as Savior.

28:40.799 --> 28:42.121
I know I can't save myself.

28:43.542 --> 28:45.003
I want Christ to be my Savior.

28:45.964 --> 28:51.730
And if you know Him, then set a goal to read His Word this year and to learn how to talk to Him.

28:52.194 --> 28:55.379
To learn how to apply Bible preaching into your life.

28:55.920 --> 28:58.865
These are the spiritual marks of maturity.

29:00.748 --> 29:07.338
I texted a friend of mine who lives and I ran this week and he accepted Christ as a savior many years ago here.

29:08.961 --> 29:09.782
And I don't text him.

29:09.802 --> 29:11.445
In fact, I haven't texted him in a long time.

29:11.505 --> 29:13.608
I just try to protect his anonymity there.

29:14.470 --> 29:16.533
But I just felt led to just send a quick text.

29:18.536 --> 29:19.698
I said, I'm praying for you.

29:21.154 --> 29:26.321
I woke up this morning and I looked at my phone there and the first text I had back was from him.

29:27.723 --> 29:29.605
He said, it's kind of crazy over here right now.

29:31.468 --> 29:36.734
He said, I sure miss our happy loving church family at Lancaster.

29:38.877 --> 29:45.586
Folks, we had a pause this morning and thank God that we're not trying to worship in a place where we have to fear telling someone else we're a Christian.

29:46.850 --> 29:53.916
When I thank God we live in a country that with all of our problems, you didn't have to worry about someone seeing you when you drove here this morning.

29:54.276 --> 30:00.342
We don't have to live in fear that we believe in Jesus Christ, that we preach the death baron resurrection of Jesus Christ.

30:00.422 --> 30:08.369
And here we have this freedom, but let's use it today to press toward the mark of knowing him more and loving him in a greater way.

30:08.409 --> 30:10.210
Paul said, I want to know Christ.

30:10.270 --> 30:12.432
This is the prize of the high calling.

30:12.492 --> 30:16.836
And I remember years ago visiting the city of Corinth, and I wanted to see what they call the Bhima seed.

30:16.816 --> 30:46.788
there, and the Bhima seed is where the judges would sit, and they would sit on this particular rock platform, and they would watch the athletes as they would come running in front of them, and when the winner would cross over the finish line, they would give them this wreath made out of olive tree branches, and they would place it onto the head of the winner, and the Apostle Paul is likening his Christian experience to running faithfully to the Lord, and looking to receive the reward from the Lord at what is called the Bhima seed, or the judgment

30:46.768 --> 30:47.929
of Jesus Christ.

30:48.009 --> 30:49.911
And Paul said that's what he was living for.

30:49.951 --> 30:53.976
He said, for to me to live as Christ and to die is gain.

30:54.036 --> 30:55.317
He wanted to know Christ.

30:55.577 --> 31:01.464
In fact, he said in 2 Corinthians 5 and verse 10, for we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ.

31:01.524 --> 31:16.740
And what I want you to realize is this wonderful new year is our opportunity to be living and preparing for that day, to be mindful that one day when we see the Lord, that we'll have the privilege of worshiping him and knowing that we were faithful to him.

31:16.720 --> 31:20.324
And so set eternal goals for your new year.

31:20.705 --> 31:22.747
And then let me say this, seek them with a passion.

31:23.709 --> 31:24.950
Seek them with a passion.

31:25.851 --> 31:32.019
I'm going to elaborate on this more tonight, but I don't believe that passion comes from knowing the why.

31:33.721 --> 31:34.602
We hear that today.

31:34.662 --> 31:36.704
Millennials want to know the why.

31:36.744 --> 31:37.766
Why, why, why, why, why?

31:37.786 --> 31:41.390
And people want to discuss and knowing the why is important.

31:42.031 --> 31:44.594
I'll grant you that, but I would submit to you

31:45.890 --> 31:47.933
knowing the who is more important.

31:50.156 --> 31:51.558
You may know all the wise.

31:51.618 --> 31:54.001
You may have all the explanations.

31:54.121 --> 31:55.743
You may be graded argumentation.

31:56.824 --> 32:00.930
But if you don't know the who, you haven't even begun.

32:00.970 --> 32:03.293
And the who is Jesus Christ.

32:04.054 --> 32:07.058
And when you know him, passion begins to develop.

32:07.426 --> 32:09.268
There's a love that springs forth.

32:09.608 --> 32:11.269
As Paul said, I'm going after this.

32:11.630 --> 32:12.170
I want to know.

32:12.270 --> 32:17.335
I remember when Terry and I fell in love and I saw her long blonde hair in Bible college there in San Dimas, California.

32:17.715 --> 32:19.557
I said, I want to get to know her a little more.

32:19.837 --> 32:22.319
Got to know when we found out we grew up in the same youth group together.

32:22.599 --> 32:26.122
My heart began to race and I began to think she might be the one.

32:26.322 --> 32:28.464
I'm telling you, I couldn't get enough time with her.

32:28.524 --> 32:28.704
Why?

32:28.925 --> 32:29.946
Because she was the who.

32:30.026 --> 32:32.368
She was the one that I wanted to know and to be with.

32:32.408 --> 32:37.412
And I'm telling you, when you understand what Jesus did for you on the cross and when you begin to fall in love

32:37.392 --> 32:41.976
with Jesus, no one has to call you and remind you and break your arm to get you to church.

32:42.016 --> 32:44.859
You wanna go where you can learn more about Jesus.

32:45.960 --> 32:47.601
And you passionately serve him.

32:48.382 --> 32:51.164
That's what Paul meant when he said, I pressed toward the mark.

32:52.526 --> 32:58.131
Frank Laubach was a missionary to the Muslims and the Philippines in 1915 and 1921.

32:59.312 --> 33:00.913
Amazing, amazing man.

33:02.455 --> 33:06.098
He found that they were having trouble telling the Filipinos

33:06.402 --> 33:08.525
to study about Jesus because they couldn't read.

33:09.507 --> 33:18.139
And so he established a literacy program that is credited with training more than 60 million Filipinos how to read.

33:19.481 --> 33:30.618
And as they began to learn how to read, they were then able to learn about Jesus Christ and tens of thousands of them turned from religion to faith in Jesus Christ as their Savior alone.

33:32.220 --> 33:36.146
He is the only American missionary to ever be remembered on a postal stamp

33:36.578 --> 33:40.483
Back in 1980, he was remembered for his great work in the Philippines.

33:42.045 --> 33:48.273
He wrote a letter to a friend as he was serving as a missionary and not seeing a lot of fruit.

33:48.433 --> 33:50.335
And I just share with you three lines and we'll be done.

33:51.717 --> 33:59.106
He said in this letter, I am disgusted with my unled self.

34:01.689 --> 34:05.394
I am disgusted with my unled self.

34:07.458 --> 34:11.804
I must surrender wholly to God.

34:14.087 --> 34:16.350
I know of no other way."

34:18.993 --> 34:20.776
Now, he had his career.

34:21.336 --> 34:22.638
He could have gone through the motions.

34:22.658 --> 34:24.541
He could have gone in at eight, gone home at five.

34:24.861 --> 34:28.666
He could have enjoyed cultures and learned languages and had a nice life.

34:28.686 --> 34:31.730
He could have just kind of gone through the motions.

34:32.098 --> 34:39.188
But when he came to that place of saying, I am disgusted with my unled self when he realized that he was pressing for nothing.

34:39.428 --> 34:41.211
He was pressing to know no one.

34:41.231 --> 34:42.913
He was not living with passion.

34:43.133 --> 34:47.440
When he then surrendered his life, holy to God and found that there was no other way.

34:47.720 --> 34:53.889
Suddenly God began to bless this man's life to the point that he touched 60 million other lives.

34:55.030 --> 35:00.658
Perhaps there's someone here this morning that needs to get disgusted with your unled self.

35:02.242 --> 35:08.328
and come to the Lord humbly and holy and say, Lord, I want to pursue you.

35:08.368 --> 35:13.593
There's lots of other trivial goals, but you are the main goal this year.

35:13.913 --> 35:19.698
You are the one thing, the one person that I want to know and that I want to serve.

35:20.059 --> 35:25.564
And all the other deeds that I do, may they all be to your glory, may they all be for you.

35:25.584 --> 35:30.409
Humility, that's when we say, I can't do it without the Lord.

35:31.209 --> 35:31.890
Focus.

35:32.450 --> 35:35.234
That's when we say, he is the one.

35:36.196 --> 35:42.246
Goals, that's the mark, the mark of knowing him and learning more of him.

35:43.067 --> 35:44.970
So think about those two goals as we close.

35:45.491 --> 35:48.776
First, think about seeing the Lord someday.

35:50.599 --> 35:52.101
Do you expect to see the Lord in heaven?

35:53.384 --> 35:56.488
Now here's what the average person would say, and I hope so.

35:57.550 --> 35:59.954
I don't want to go to the other place, and that's very wise deduction.

36:02.818 --> 36:05.360
But the Bible says you actually can know that you're gonna see the Lord.

36:05.861 --> 36:12.107
The Bible says these things have a written unto you that believe on the name of the Son of God that you may know that you have eternal life.

36:13.929 --> 36:18.013
Now, if there's anything we would want to know, it should be that we have eternal life.

36:18.053 --> 36:20.535
That's something we should want to know.

36:20.575 --> 36:28.043
In fact, it says in John 1, 12, as many as received him to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name.

36:29.864 --> 36:31.506
So I would encourage you today

36:31.778 --> 36:44.657
to settle this fact that you have believed on his name, that you're not trusting in the Baptist church, the Catholic church, any church, but that you have put your souls keeping in the safe, powerful hands of Jesus Christ.

36:45.698 --> 36:56.594
Make sure that you're ready to see him, and if you're knowing in your heart that you're gonna see him, then make sure that you are reaching forth this year to know him.

36:57.378 --> 37:05.616
Now tonight I'll share many goals and many different visions of the church, but let me just say, if we're not reaching for Christ, none of the rest of it will matter.

37:06.258 --> 37:10.527
Reaching forth in 2020 to know Him, to live for Him.

